<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>PDFUnicorn - convert your data to PDF</title>
	%= include 'site/head'
	%= include 'mixpanel'
  
    <!-- record main page view -->
  	<script type="text/javascript">mixpanel.track('view-main-page')</script>
</head>

<body>
	%= include 'site/header'

    <div class="container">

      <!-- Main component for a primary marketing message or call to action -->
      <div class="jumbotron">
        <h2>Convert your data to PDF</h2>
        
        <form action="" method="post">
        	<div class="col-sm-6">
<textarea name="data" style="width: 100%; height: 400px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px">
data:
  visitor:
    name: You
</textarea>
        	</div>
        	<div class="col-sm-6">
<textarea name="template" style="width: 100%; height: 400px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 16px">
<doc>
    <style>
      page:
        margin: 5
        padding: 5
        border: 0
        border-radius: 10
      row:
        margin: 5
        padding: 5
        border: 0
        border-radius: 8
      cell:
        margin: 5
        padding: 5
        border: 1
        border-radius: 5
      class:
        red:
          background-color: #FFEEEE
        green:
          background-color: #EEFFEE
        blue:
          background-color: #EEEEFF
        no-pad:
          padding: 0
        no-marg:
          margin: 0
        section:
          padding: 15
    </style>
    <page>
        <row>
	        <cell class="section" span="12">
		        <row class="no-marg">
		            <cell class="section" span="12">
		            	First up, thank you for your interest in PDF Unicorn. You action has pinged a server that will change a graph that will make me smile. 8)
		            	
		            	Generating PDFs on the fly is not a simple thing, so I'm having a go at making it at least a little easier.
		            	
		            	PDF Unicorn allows you to build templates and add data to generate PDF documents.  
		            </cell>
		        </row>
		        <row class="no-marg">
		            <cell class="section" span="12">
		            	First up, thank you for your interest in PDF Unicorn. You action has pinged a server that will change a graph that will make me smile. 8)
		            	
		            	Generating PDFs on the fly is not a simple thing, so I'm having a go at making it at least a little easier.
		            	
		            	PDF Unicorn allows you to build templates and add data to generate PDF documents.  
		            </cell>
		        </row>
            </cell>
        </row>
        
        <row>
            <cell class="red" span="12">
            	A page is made up of rows, cells, text, and images.
            	The page, row, and cell containing this text all have 5px margins and padding.
            	Margins go outside the element's border and padding is inside.
            </cell>
        </row>
        <row class="green no-pad">
            <cell class="red no-pad" span="12">
            	Row and cell padding have been removed here.
            </cell>
        </row>
        <row class="green no-pad no-marg">
            <cell class="red no-pad no-marg" span="12">
            	Row and cell padding and margin have been removed here.
            </cell>
        </row>
        <row class="green no-marg">
            <cell class="red" span="12">
            	The borders of adjascent elements overlap if those elements have no margin.
            </cell>
        </row>
        <row class="green no-marg">
            <cell class="red no-marg" span="12">
            	Turn off the cell border
            </cell>
        </row>
        <row class="green no-pad">
            <cell class="red no-marg" span="12">
            	Put the cell padding and row margin back..
            </cell>
        </row>
        <row class="green">
            <cell class="red">By</cell>
            <cell class="red">default</cell>
            <cell class="red">each</cell>
            <cell class="red">row</cell>
            <cell class="red">is</cell>
            <cell class="red" span="2">comprised</cell>
            <cell class="red">of</cell>
            <cell class="red" span="2">twelve</cell>
            <cell class="red" span="2">columns</cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell span="3">
            	A cell may span more than 1 column.
            	When the text in a cell is too wide to fit, the text is wrapped and the cell is made taller to fit the wrapped text.
            </cell>
            <cell span="3">Did I mention we have rounded corners too?!</cell>
            <cell span="6">
            	Other cells' height will be increased to the tallest cell's height.
            </cell>
        </row>
    </page>
</doc>
</textarea>
        	</div>
        	<div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 20px">
        		<input style="margin-top: 20px" type="submit" value="Get PDF Here">
        	</div>
        </form>

      </div>

    </div> <!-- /container -->


    <!-- Bootstrap core JavaScript
    ================================================== -->
    <!-- Placed at the end of the document so the pages load faster -->
    <script src="/lib/jquery/jquery.js"></script>
    <script src="/lib/bootstrap/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>

</body>
</html>
